### Instruction:
How do you align a row of divs to the right using flex in css?  Show me an example.

### Response:

To align a row of div to the right using flexbox, we can use CSS properties like display, padding, margin and border. Here is an example code that demonstrates how to do this:
```css
div.container {
background-color: #3456;
background-image: url('/images/flexbox_example');
}

div#content p {
margin: 20px 108px;
padding: 20px;
border: 1px solid;
}
```
This code sets the background color of the container to #3456 and adds an image link to the URL '/images/flexbox_example'. It also sets the margin and padding of the p element inside the container to 20px and 108px respectively.

